{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Light barbecue or preheat grill (220°C).","Place onions, ginger, garlic and chilli in mixing bowl then chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>.","Add mango, tamarind paste, treacle, allspice, red wine and orange juice then cook <b>25 min\/98°C\/speed <b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add vinegar and, without measuring cup, cook <b>10 min\/100°C\/speed <b>. Insert measuring cup then blend <b>1 min\/speed 10<b>.","Place lamb chops on barbecue or under a hot grill (220°C). When charred, flip over and char other side.","Brush each chop generously with tamarind and mango sauce then move to cooler part of barbecue, or lower under the grill. Cook for 5-8 minutes, turning over halfway to baste other side. Serve immediately or keep warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["70 g onions, quartered","10 g fresh root ginger, peeled, cut in round slices (2 mm)","1 garlic clove","1 jalapeño chilli, fresh, halved, deseeded","1 ripe mango, large, cut in pieces","3 Tbsp tamarind paste","4 Tbsp treacle","¼ tsp ground allspice","90 g red wine","180 g orange juice","2 Tbsp red wine vinegar","24 lamb chops"]}],"id":"r95376","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-0dsiC2W0Se8\/XZQwi31XEqI\/AAAAAAAAcmo\/zruElqg8l4Q1x7VvN9__Fx-qcM9LI_LEQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_aok_oSa3fwYwUXcg.png","title":"Tamarind and Chilli Barbecued Lamb Chops","publishedAt":"2016-05-30T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"14.3 g","fat":"18.4 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"4.1 g","calories":"1002 kJ \/ 240 kcal"},"usefulItems":"pastry brush, grill","hintsAndTricks":["Add extra jalapeños or hotter chillies for more heat."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","55m","24 pieces"]}